---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Mutation Engine">
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="section-title">Mutation Engine</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">Phase 1 Walkthrough - Part 3 of 4</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>The Heart of the System</h3>
        <p>
          The mutate function is the core of everything.
          It produces a new tree version with only the path nodes cloned.
          Siblings stay shared via Arc pointers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="diagram">
        <pre class="ascii-art">
// Function signature
pub fn mutate(root: DomNode, path: Vecusize, change: F) -> DomNode
    where F: FnOnce
    mutate_recursive(root, path, 0, change)
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Parameters</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><code>root</code> - The tree to mutate (Arc pointer)</li>
          <li><code>path</code> - Indices to follow (e.g., 0,1 means "child 0, then child 1")</li>
          <li><code>change</code> - Closure that modifies the target node</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Recursive Implementation</h2>

      <div class="diagram">
        <pre class="ascii-art">
fn mutate_recursive(node, path, depth, change):
    if path.is_empty():
        // Base case: reached target node
        new_node = node.clone()     // Clone node data
        change(new_node)              // Apply change
        return Arc(new_node)         // Wrap in new Arc
    else:
        // Recursive case: follow the path
        child_idx = path[0]
        new_node = node.clone()       // Shallow clone

        if child exists:
            new_child = mutate_recursive(child, path[1..], depth+1, change)
            new_node.children = new_node.children.update(child_idx, new_child)

        return Arc(new_node)
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Key Insight</h3>
        <p>
          node.clone() clones the Node fields. The child Arc pointers
          are copied by reference. When we call .update() on ImVector,
          we get a new vector sharing all unchanged indices with the old one.
          Only the path gets new Arc allocations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Trace Example</h2>

      <div class="diagram">
        <pre class="ascii-art">
// Tree: root -> child[0] -> child[0][0]
// Call: mutate(root, [0, 0], change)

1. mutate_recursive(root, [0, 0])
   - path not empty
   - clone root -> new_root
   - recurse on root.children[0] with path [0]

2. mutate_recursive(child[0], [0])
   - path not empty
   - clone child[0] -> new_child0
   - recurse on child[0].children[0] with path []

3. mutate_recursive(child[0][0], [])
   - path empty! Base case
   - clone leaf -> new_leaf
   - apply change
   - return Arc(new_leaf)

// Back up the stack:

4. new_child0.children[0] = new_leaf (from step 3)
5. new_root.children[0] = Arc(new_child0)

// Result: root, child[0], and leaf[0] are NEW Arcs
// Siblings of the path remain SHARED via original Arc pointers
        </pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Test Results</h2>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>test_mutation_returns_new_arc</h3>
        <p>old root ptr: <code class="highlight">0x24b4f07d0b0</code></p>
        <p>new root ptr: <code class="highlight">0x24b4f07d380</code></p>
        <p>Differferent pointers - mutation produces new tree</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>test_untouched_siblings_are_shared</h3>
        <p>shared sibling (child0): <code class="shared">0x23933bde130</code></p>
        <p>Arc::ptr_eq returns true - same allocation</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>test_mutated_path_is_new</h3>
        <p>old leaf: <code>0x2b1ddde8bd0</code></p>
        <p>new leaf: <code>0x2b1dddeb2b0</code></p>
        <p>Mutated path nodes get NEW Arc pointers</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

   <div class="container text-center mb-xl">
     <a href="../proof" class="hero-cta">Next: The Proof Test</a>
   </div>
</DocsLayout>